package com.abstruction.java;

public abstract class Bank {
		public abstract void savings();

		public abstract void current();

		public abstract void salary();

		public abstract void joint();

		public void branchDetails() {
			System.out.println("Kolkata");
		}
	}
		
/**Hiding the implementation part is called abstraction 
it has 2 types, 
1.Partially abstraction(abstract class) 
2.Fully abstraction(interface)
It can have abstract methods (no body)
It can have concrete methods (with body) non abstract
Only abstract methods (before Java 8)
Default & static methods (Java 8+)
we cannot create an object of an abstract class.
any access specifier allowed
abstract → must be overridden(final not allowed)
**/